Mindlin Licence: Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 DOI: http://dx.doi.org/10.4279/PIP.050001www.papersinphysics.org ISSN 1852-4249 LT2C2: A language of thought with Turing-computable Kolmogorov complexity Sergio Romano,1∗Mariano Sigman,2,3†Santiago Figueira1,3‡ In this paper, we present a theoretical eﬀort to connect the t heory of program size to psychology by implementing a concrete language of thought w ith Turing-computable Kol- mogorov complexity (LT2C2) satisfying the following requirements: 1) to be simple eno ugh so that the complexity of any given ﬁnite binary sequence can be computed, 2) to be based on tangible operations of human reasoning ( printing,repeating ,...), 3) to be suﬃciently powerful to generate all possible sequences but not too powe rful as to identify regulari- ties which would be invisible to humans.
